***** PLL 0 *****

Instance Name                 : AxiPLL
Resource                      : PLL_TR0
Locked Pin Name               : PllLocked[1]
Clock Source                  : external
Reference Clock Resource      : GPIOR_118
Reference Clock               : AxiPllClkIn
Feedback Mode                 : internal

Reference Clock Frequency     : 12.0000 MHz
Reference Clock Period        : 83.3333 ns
Multiplier (M)                : 112
Pre-Divider (N)               : 1
VCO Frequency                 : 1344.0000 MHz
Post-Divider (O)              : 2
PLL Frequency                 : 672.0000 MHz

Output Clock 0
Clock Pin Name                : Axi0Clk
Output Divider                : 7
Output Phase Shift            : 0
Output Frequency              : 96.0000 MHz
Output Period                 : 10.417 ns

Output Clock 1
Clock Pin Name                : tx_slowclk
Output Divider                : 14
Output Phase Shift            : 0
Output Frequency              : 48.0000 MHz
Output Period                 : 20.833 ns

Output Clock 2
Clock Pin Name                : tx_fastclk
Output Divider                : 4
Output Phase Shift            : 90
Output Frequency              : 168.0000 MHz
Output Period                 : 5.952 ns

Frequency calculations:
	VCO = REFCLK * (M/N)
	    = 12.0000 MHz * (112/1)
	    = 1344.0000 MHz
	PLL = VCO / O
	    = 1344.0000 MHz / 2
	    = 672.0000 MHz

	CLKOUT0 = PLL / CLKOUT0_DIV
	        = 672.0000 MHz / 7
	        = 96.0000 MHz
	CLKOUT1 = PLL / CLKOUT1_DIV
	        = 672.0000 MHz / 14
	        = 48.0000 MHz
	CLKOUT2 = PLL / CLKOUT2_DIV
	        = 672.0000 MHz / 4
	        = 168.0000 MHz

SDC Constraints:
	create_clock -period 10.417 -name Axi0Clk [get_ports {Axi0Clk}]
	create_clock -period 20.833 -name tx_slowclk [get_ports {tx_slowclk}]
	create_clock -waveform {1.488 4.464} -period 5.952 -name tx_fastclk [get_ports {tx_fastclk}]

